The paper deals with downlink precoding and power allocation strategies for a multi-cell multi-user massive Full-Dimension MIMO network. This involves utilizing channel reciprocity and estimation of signal parameters via rotational invariance technique (ESPRIT) for uplink direction of arrival (DoA) estimation. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), Systems and Control (cs.SY), Multimedia (cs.MM), and Computer Communications (cs.COM) sub-categories.
